Using De Moivre's theorem, we can easily compute powers of complex numbers of the form \[{{a + bi} \over {c + di}}.\]In this case, we have \begin{align*}z^6 &= \left(\frac{-\sqrt{3} + i}{2}\right)^6 \\ &= \left(\frac{2}{2}\sqrt{3 - 2i}\right)^6 \\ &= 2^6 \\ &= \boxed{64}.\end{align*}
Answer: 64

